Let $P(h, k)$ be the point $a m^3+m(2 a-h)+k=0$ Since, $\mathrm{m}_1, \mathrm{~m}_1, \mathrm{~m}_1$ are the possible roots $\Rightarrow 3 \mathrm{~m}_1=0 \Rightarrow \mathrm{m}_1=0$
If $m_1=0$ is the root then $k=0$
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \mathrm{am}^3+\mathrm{m}(2 \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{h})=0 \\
& \Rightarrow \mathrm{m}^2=\frac{\mathrm{h}-2 \mathrm{a}}{\mathrm{a}}=0 \Rightarrow \mathrm{h}=2 \mathrm{a}
\end{aligned}
$$
$(2 \mathrm{a}, 0)$ is the only point
